 AS BIRDS THAT ENTERING BY THE CHIMNEY, AND FINDING THEMSELVES INCLOSED IN A CHAMBER,
 FLUTTER AT THE FALSE LIGHT OF A GLASSE WINDOW,
 FOR WANT OF WIT TO CONSIDER WHICH WAY THEY CAME IN....
